description: Love may conquer all, but it’s pure animal lust that keeps things interesting! In offices and bedrooms all over town, a doctor makes a play for a snotty young model, while a business director can’t keep his hands off the man he’s known since childhood.  Men from all walks of life are secretly seducing and being seduced! A few of these match-ups are filled with real, lasting love... and a few are simply moments of unchecked passion. Can you tell them apart?
name: Vol. 1

description: Trapped on an island consumed by a super virus, The New Mutants fall one by one to the monstrous infection and begin to change. Can Warlock keep the virus in check, even if it means going against his friends?
name: Contami-Nation

description: Sweet, delicate flowers and killer animals…they spring to life on the tattooed backs of the underworld’s most infamous men. But does love have a chance to bloom in a world of sin that’s steeped in perpetual inky night? And in the midst of the crime-filled chaos, is there a passion so powerful that it can lift a soul right out if its body?
name: Vol. 1

description: Will Sentarou Katsura be able to keep his promise to make Sanshirou Sakamoto happy? As Sakamoto's father continuously tries to match him with potential brides, and Takasugi warning Sakamoto that Sentaro will leave him someday, will the two ever be able to be together alone? Plus, everybody’s favorite darlings from the hit OVA– Takasugui x Ogata, Shikibu x Tsutsumi, Todoroki x Takeru, and Kitasenju x Juujou – all return in this madcap manga.
name: Vol. 1

description: Young Mr. Ida might be a newbie teacher but he is capable enough. Problem is, every time he writes his lecture on the board, he feels this deeply intense gaze boring through the back of his head. Could he be doing something wrong? For huge and intimidating student Kobayashi, Mr. Ida can’t do anything wrong. In fact, Ida is Kobayashi’s Mr. Right. From the creator of the award-winning Antique Bakery series comes this whimsical boys’ love story that will have readers feeling good in no time. Sometimes plain, sometimes witty, sometimes bitter, sometimes sweet…
name: Vol. 1

description: Kobayashi, Toyo, Ida, Hashizume and Rikuko… everyone has gotten a little older but are they any wiser? The loveable characters of The Moon and the Sandals saga begin a new chapter in their lives. Kobayashi and Toyo have both successfully started their careers, Hashizume now heads his own restaurant and Rikuko is studying to be a doctor. But amidst all this seeming success, old issues still lurk below the surface, waiting to be resolved. Question is… Will the gang be able to muster enough maturity to finally settle old scores?
name: Vol. 2

description:
Escape from the Eighth City...escape from Hell! K'un-Lun is the majestic city of otherworldly kung-fu champions, the spiritual home of the Iron Fist and a repository of centuries-old wisdom. But for many of those centuries, K'un-Lun's leaders have used the Eighth City - a secret plane with only one way in and no way out - as a dumping ground...to offload their murderers, monsters and demons. But as Danny Rand has just learned, it has also been the prison of K'un-Lun's political prisoners. And this is a historical shame that cannot stand. The current regime of K'un-Lun has sent Rand and his band of immortal fighters from the Seven Cities to recover the political prisoners - including perhaps the very first Iron Fist - but it is a death mission for which there may be no return...or salvation!

Collects The Immortal Iron Fist #21-27.

  • Hardcover release date: August 26, 2009
  • Trade paperback release date: November 25, 2009
name: Volume 5

volume.name: The Immortal Iron Fist: Escape From the Eighth City

description: In issue #2 of the NEW series based on the cult-classic horror/adventure film, Ashley J. Williams continues his battle against the malevolent forces behind the Evil Dead. While Ash is pushed to the limit by a Deadite biker gang in Oklahoma, a young boy in Brazil becomes a pawn in a ploy to resurrect an ancient evil not seen since World War 2! New adventures! New menaces! New weapons! It's better than the "blue light special" at your local S-Mart, baby!

Among the dark pyramids in Bayuda, Sudan, part of the ancient Kingdom of Kush, archeologist Matthew Shady finds an archaic engraving with the name of an immortal prince, quite similar to that of an elusive enemy of Dampyr's... In guerrilla-stricken Darfur, Harlan and Kurjak are guests of the refugee camp run by their friends from the “Medical Team”. They inquire into an old Sahara legend, while Tesla goes to Bayuda excavations with Professor Lagu, curator of the Khartoum Museum. In the tombs under Bayuda pyramids, abominable creatures are awakening, and they will unleash destruction on the unfortunate archeologist camp...
name: La sovrana dei regni neri

description: Once upon a time in the desert, when the land was crossed by salt- and gold-laden caravans, there was one oasis no one dared to enter. Travellers stayed away from it, considering the place a realm of death and danger. The lost oasis of Zerzura, in the Great Sands Sea, was fabled in ancient Arab books and considered a place haunted by the djinns, the demons of the desert. For decades European explorers – such as the members of the Zerzura Club and the Desert Patrol: Major Bagnold, Count Almasy, and Prince Kemal El Din – went looking for the oasis to no avail. Today: While in the remote lands of Nubia Matthew Shady is under the influence of the charming Kushite Queen Nawidemak, and Tesla is fighting a devilish lion-god, Harlan and Kurjak are in Darfur, looking for some trace of the mysterious oasis. The only people who can help them are the beautiful and brave Samantha King, grand-granddaughter of explorer Harding King, and her friend Cameron, retired British SAS soldier. A new Desert Patrol is forming, to confront the dangers of the Sahara and find the legendary Zerzura...
name: La pattuglia del deserto

description: In the Great Sands Sea, the adventurous patrol led by Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak is sieged by the cruel Janjaweed outlaws, who were promised by the Master of the Night Vathek – disguised as the mysterious Great Amir – to live an eternal life of pleasures after death. Vathek is hiding in the lost oasis of Zerzura. If our heroes manage to reach it, they will be facing new threats inside the legendary White CIty: an endless army of dead warriors, led by the Master himself, who’s endowed with uncanny powers and capable of any kind of transformation...
name: L’oasi perduta

description: As an ancestral heritage, isolated villages in Corsica still have their own shamans. They’re called “mazzéri” and are endowed with a terrible power: they can kill people in their dreams. While she’s in Corsica for her anthropological researches, the charming Sophie Mutter becomes obsessed by the gaze of a mysterious woman. During the night, in the village of Falcinaccia, Sophie witnesses a horrendous ghost parade and is taken inside a dream, through wild forests and harsh mountains: the hunt begins! The wolf killed by the girl will show the face of her beloved Harlan and, on waking up, Sophie will find herself smeared in blood and mud: the horror begins! Harlan’s fate is doomed. The wound he suffered in the dream is spreading like a cancer, death is getting near, and nothing can avoid Sophie her fate of calamitous prophetess; an army of dead “mazzéri” threatens to decimate the people of Falcinaccia in an oneiric battle, the bloody “mandrache”...
name: I cacciatori del sogno

description: First Oor Wullie volume, published in 1940.

Harlan, Kurjak and Tesla go back to Colombia, where they meet with an old friend, policeman Bobby Quintana. Our heroes are confronted with dangerous gangsters and have to solve the puzzle of an intricated dope business. This time, though, it's not about an usual narcotic. They will have to face the consequences of the horrible “hierba negra”— this drug allows it drinker to come back from the dead inside another person's body, but just for one night. Scheming in the darkness, plotting the death of the Dampyr, it's one of his cruelest enemies...
name: La macumba dei narcos

description: It's a nasty case of possession by a greed-driven ghost, and one of the Ghostbusters is its new vessel! It's a battle of wills on the mental plane in this latest issue of the hit ongoing Ghostbusters series!
name: Possesion for Ghosts

description: The Mad Hatter's throwing a party...a search party, for his "Alice!" Unfortunately for her, his first invitee is Vicki Vale, still in Arkham City after the helicopter crash. Once she's intercepted by Tweedledee and Tweedledumb, will she be able to RSVP "NO" or is her fate sealed? And who else unlucky enough to be on his guest list?!
name: Vicki in Wonderland (Part 1)

description: An attack on a large supermarket triggers panic among the last straggling customers shortly before closing time. It was supposed to be a quick job but the police block off all getaway routes and the armed robbery very soon turns into a siege. There is mounting tension. Demian tries absolutely everything within his power to save the hostages, and the bandits reluctantly have to admit to themselves that they’ve made a terrible mistake…
name: La sindrome di Stoccolma

description: A magical night, the appearance of a mysterious dancing girl, and Gaston Velasco’s life changes for ever. After a long and dangerous journey, Demian goes with his best friend along the coast of North Africa to honor the tomb of the sweetheart Gaston loved more than any other. But someone, out in the desert, is awaiting their arrival. And an ancient hatred explodes in the recollection of the… Star of Algiers!
name: La Stella di Algeri

description: Jade: the most fascinating and lethal of murderesses. The news of her arrival is disquieting even for bloodthirsty Jean-Luc Corsari. While Chinese and Japanese criminals prepare for warfare on the streets of Marseille, Demian hastens to the help of Marie, only to find himself caught up together with her in a deadly confrontation between the Triads and the Yakuza!
name: Yakuza!

description:
Contents:

  • Baker's Half Dozen
  • Topps On Two Wheels
  • Quick On The Draw was a Western
  • The £l,000,000 Challenge
  • Speedboy
  • The Fastest Footballer On Earth
  • Journey To The Stars
  • Death Wish
name: Speed #1

description: Who is Marcel Gaillard? The only things known about him are that he's a blond-haired bike rider, who joins a meeting of dangerous mercenaries... Demian, under the alias of Gaillard, goes to a Central African state, where he must try to avoid the escalation of an old tribal feud into a bloody genocide. Beyond the walls of an army-sieged hospital in the middle of nowhere, he'll meet a very attractive old friend...
name: La pista degli sciacalli
